{"TopicId":135387,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"Will ksp run on these graphics on 1.1?","CreatedByName":"corporelax","CreatedById":136704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T18:43:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"corporelax","CreatedById":136704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T18:43:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022line-height:1.6;\u0022\u003ECause I have a bad one.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy Processor is Intel(R) Core(TM) i3-4005U CPU @ 1.70GHz\u00A0\u00A0 1.70 GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstalled RAM 4.00 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSystem type\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 64-bit operating system, x64-based processor\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill this be good for KSP 1.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-31T20:55:04Z\u0022 title=\u002203/31/2016 08:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by corporelax\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EGrammar error\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:05:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222483035\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459363398\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136704\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022corporelax\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, corporelax said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill Kerbal Space Program better for bad PCs after the 1.1 update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCause I have a bad one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy Processor is Intel(R) Core(TM) i3-4005U CPU @ 1.70GHz\u00A0\u00A0 1.70 GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstalled RAM 4.00 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSystem type\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 64-bit operating system, x64-based processor\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill this be good for KSP 1.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you\u0027ll need a better processor and maybe 2 gb more ram so you have some breathing room.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, rename it \u0022Will this run KSP 1.1?\u0022, it\u0027ll make more sense that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-30T19:06:56Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2016 07:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"corporelax","CreatedById":136704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T20:41:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222483094\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459364756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/30/2016 at 11:05 PM, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you\u0027ll need a better processor and maybe 2 gb more ram so you have some breathing room.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, rename it \u0022Will this run KSP 1.1?\u0022, it\u0027ll make more sense that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok but can it be; May ksp run on these graphics on 1.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T20:42:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222485961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459456885\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136704\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022corporelax\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, corporelax said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok but can it be; May ksp run on these graphics on 1.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-31T20:43:40Z\u0022 title=\u002203/31/2016 08:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb Coleman","CreatedById":140612,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T22:38:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about me? My system runs at 12.5fps whenever I have more than 100 parts. My system:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nintel pentium D 940\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nATi Radeon HD 6450\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4GB\u00A0ram 3.25GB useable\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwindows 10 32bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camacha","CreatedById":59088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T23:15:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is the video card, if any?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T23:19:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy system runs at 2-6 fps with more than 80 parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAMD E-350 Processor 1.60GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6.00 gb RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n64-bit operating system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDirectX 11\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what about me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camacha","CreatedById":59088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T23:23:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222486220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459463894\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022140612\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jeb Coleman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, Jeb Coleman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about me? My system runs at 12.5fps whenever I have more than 100 parts. My system:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nintel pentium D 940\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose Pentium D\u0027s are oldies. An upgrade to something relatively modest, but modern, like a Pentium G3258, should yield a massive performance increase. It should not cost an arm and a leg either.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: a quick check reveals that these Pentium D\u0027s are 10 years old. In reality even a little bit older, since they are quite literally two Pentium 4\u0027s stuck together.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"11of10","CreatedById":90592,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T10:08:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about AMD A4-5300 APU with 6GB RAM?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr rather, why does it go into yellow as soon as I make a rover with over 40 parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"corporelax","CreatedById":136704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T12:51:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222487159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459505315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290592\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002211of10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, 11of10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about AMD A4-5300 APU with 6GB RAM?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr rather, why does it go into yellow as soon as I make a rover with over 40 parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a Laptop\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"11of10","CreatedById":90592,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T12:55:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDesktop\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Harry Rhodan","CreatedById":119953,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T13:45:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222487159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459505315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290592\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002211of10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, 11of10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about AMD A4-5300 APU with 6GB RAM?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr rather, why does it go into yellow as soon as I make a rover with over 40 parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause AMD processors have been comparatively slow over the last few years and that was their cheapest entry level chip at that time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"11of10","CreatedById":90592,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T19:02:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDarn it, that I didn\u0027t know! Hmm... seems a new CPU is in order\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EliasDanger","CreatedById":151803,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T20:06:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP runs pretty smooth with my current gen i5 and gtx 980 ti. So just get that and you\u0027ll be fine. Ditch the potatoes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"11of10","CreatedById":90592,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-01T21:45:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni5 is a bit out of my budget, for now at least. And to think that this current CPU was more than good when it was bought... goshdarnittoheck\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RA3236","CreatedById":150734,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T02:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow well would KSP 1.1 run on these specs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n2x Intel\u00A0Core T2 Duo CPU T9300 at\u00A02.50GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0px;\u0022\u003E\nATI Mobility Radeon HD2600\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0px;\u0022\u003E\n4GB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camacha","CreatedById":59088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T03:22:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222488235\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459537331\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290592\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002211of10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, 11of10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDarn it, that I didn\u0027t know! Hmm... seems a new CPU is in order\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease, wait until we know what 1.1 actually does. It will likely bring a performance increase for most people, especially those with CPU\u0027s with a weak single threaded performance. This is absolutely the worst time to randomly start buying hardware. 1.1 might very well increase performance on the same hardware, and it will almost certainly change the type of PC that will run KSP well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wait and see. Holding out is the only sensible course of action at the moment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"11of10","CreatedById":90592,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T09:22:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if I do get a new CPU, it\u0027ll be thoroughly researched before that, don\u0027t worry, and thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny thing tho, exactly the same physics slowdown happens in both 1.0.5 and 1.1 prerelease with the same craft, even when I rebuild it completely from scratch... Even if the rest of the game performs much better!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"corporelax","CreatedById":136704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T11:33:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u00A0\u003Cu\u003EDO NOT\u003C/u\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Eknow how it will perform on those graphics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I think this is the recommended specs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n64 bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.4 GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n16 GB ram\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camacha","CreatedById":59088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T12:03:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222489886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459596829\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136704\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022corporelax\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, corporelax said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u00A0\u003Cu\u003EDO NOT\u003C/u\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Eknow how it will perform on those graphics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I think this is the recommended specs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n64 bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.4 GHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n16 GB ram\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n64 bit is the only one that ,makes any sense. GHz says nothing without additional information about the architecture, generation and model. 16 GB is huge overkill. I doubt that even the most enthusiastic player with a massively modded install will ever reach 8 GB.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cantab","CreatedById":104935,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T12:19:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, the Windows specs on Steam are as follows:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMinimum:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003EWindows Vista or 7\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessor:\u003C/strong\u003ECore 2 Duo\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMemory:\u003C/strong\u003E3GB RAM\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EGraphics:\u003C/strong\u003ESM3 512MB VRAM\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHard Drive:\u003C/strong\u003E4 GB HD space\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommended:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003EWindows 8 or 10 64 bit\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessor:\u003C/strong\u003ECore i5\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMemory:\u003C/strong\u003E4 GB RAM\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EGraphics:\u003C/strong\u003ESM4 1GB VRAM\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHard Drive:\u003C/strong\u003E6 GB HD space\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-02T12:19:55Z\u0022 title=\u002204/02/2016 12:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by cantab\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camacha","CreatedById":59088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-02T12:24:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222489939\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459599545\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104935\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022c